<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="291" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1350,1986]" box="[151,759,1384,1410]" pageId="0" pageNumber="291">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,759,1384,1410]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="291" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,759,1384,1410]" pageId="0" pageNumber="291">
<taxonomicName authority="Chen &amp; Du" authorityName="Du" authorityYear="2017" box="[151,494,1384,1410]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Sweltsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamula" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,342,1384,1410]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="291">Sweltsa hamula</emphasis>
Chen &amp; Du
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[507,600,1384,1410]" pageId="0" pageNumber="291" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[618,744,1384,1410]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStart-1="FIGURES 10 – 11" captionStartId-0="1.[151,258,1270,1292]" captionStartId-1="1.[151,258,1358,1380]" captionTargetBox-0="[317,1260,424,1241]" captionTargetId-0="figure@1.[313,1273,418,1249]" captionTargetPageId-0="1" captionText-0="FIGURES 1 – 9. Sweltsa hamula, sp. nov., holotype. 1. Male habitus, dorsal view; 2. Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; 3. Wings; 4. Male terminalia, dorsal view; 5. Male terminalia, dorsolateral view; 6. Epiproct, dorsal view; 7. Epiproct, lateral view; 8. Aedeagus, ventral view; 9. Male terminalia, ventral view." captionText-1="FIGURES 10 – 11. Sweltsa hamula, sp. nov., paratype. 10. Male terminalia, dorsal view; 11. Male terminalia, dorsolateral view." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/1018810/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="291">Figs. 1–11</figureCitation>
.)
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1350,1986]" pageId="0" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,315,1419,1442]" pageId="0" pageNumber="291">Adult habitus.</emphasis>
Triocellate. General color brown. Head with dark brown stigmas; compound eyes dark, ocelli with dark margins; antennae brown (
<figureCitation box="[434,537,1451,1474]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1270,1292]" captionTargetBox="[317,1260,424,1241]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[313,1273,418,1249]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Sweltsa hamula, sp. nov., holotype. 1. Male habitus, dorsal view; 2. Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; 3. Wings; 4. Male terminalia, dorsal view; 5. Male terminalia, dorsolateral view; 6. Epiproct, dorsal view; 7. Epiproct, lateral view; 8. Aedeagus, ventral view; 9. Male terminalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1018810/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="291">Figs. 1–2</figureCitation>
). Pronotum with symmetrical rugosities and dark margins; meso- and metanota with dark U-marks. Wings hyaline, Rs of forewing branched, anal field of hindwing small and folded with three veins (
<figureCitation box="[1357,1422,1483,1506]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1270,1292]" captionTargetBox="[317,1260,424,1241]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[313,1273,418,1249]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Sweltsa hamula, sp. nov., holotype. 1. Male habitus, dorsal view; 2. Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; 3. Wings; 4. Male terminalia, dorsal view; 5. Male terminalia, dorsolateral view; 6. Epiproct, dorsal view; 7. Epiproct, lateral view; 8. Aedeagus, ventral view; 9. Male terminalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1018810/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="291">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Tergum 1 to anterior of tergum 8 with a continuous, brown median stripe (
<figureCitation box="[943,1006,1515,1538]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1270,1292]" captionTargetBox="[317,1260,424,1241]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[313,1273,418,1249]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Sweltsa hamula, sp. nov., holotype. 1. Male habitus, dorsal view; 2. Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; 3. Wings; 4. Male terminalia, dorsal view; 5. Male terminalia, dorsolateral view; 6. Epiproct, dorsal view; 7. Epiproct, lateral view; 8. Aedeagus, ventral view; 9. Male terminalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1018810/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="291">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Cerci brown with long setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="291" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1350,1986]" pageId="0" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,263,1547,1570]" pageId="0" pageNumber="291">Male.</emphasis>
Body length 8.5–9.0 mm; forewings length 8.0– 
<quantity box="[800,885,1547,1570]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" pageId="0" pageNumber="291" unit="mm" value="8.5">8.5 mm</quantity>
, hindwings length 7.0– 
<quantity box="[1142,1228,1547,1570]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="0" pageNumber="291" unit="mm" value="7.5">7.5 mm</quantity>
. Tergum 9 with an upraised, medially notched transverse ridge (
<figureCitation box="[635,739,1579,1602]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1270,1292]" captionTargetBox="[317,1260,424,1241]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[313,1273,418,1249]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Sweltsa hamula, sp. nov., holotype. 1. Male habitus, dorsal view; 2. Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; 3. Wings; 4. Male terminalia, dorsal view; 5. Male terminalia, dorsolateral view; 6. Epiproct, dorsal view; 7. Epiproct, lateral view; 8. Aedeagus, ventral view; 9. Male terminalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1018810/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="291">Figs. 4–5</figureCitation>
). Tergum 10 divided, median portion forming a sclerotized area. From dorsal aspect, epiproct sub-elliptical and with thin lateral margins on basal half, then gradually tapered to a sharp apex; mesally, epiproct with dense hairs (
<figureCitation box="[595,698,1643,1666]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1270,1292]" captionTargetBox="[317,1260,424,1241]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[313,1273,418,1249]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Sweltsa hamula, sp. nov., holotype. 1. Male habitus, dorsal view; 2. Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; 3. Wings; 4. Male terminalia, dorsal view; 5. Male terminalia, dorsolateral view; 6. Epiproct, dorsal view; 7. Epiproct, lateral view; 8. Aedeagus, ventral view; 9. Male terminalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1018810/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="291">Figs. 4, 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[711,741,1643,1666]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 11" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1358,1380]" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 11. Sweltsa hamula, sp. nov., paratype. 10. Male terminalia, dorsal view; 11. Male terminalia, dorsolateral view." pageId="0" pageNumber="291">10</figureCitation>
). In lateral aspect, epiproct constricted basally and sub-medially, apically back curved, forming a hook-shaped apex (
<figureCitation box="[723,830,1675,1698]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1270,1292]" captionTargetBox="[317,1260,424,1241]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[313,1273,418,1249]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Sweltsa hamula, sp. nov., holotype. 1. Male habitus, dorsal view; 2. Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; 3. Wings; 4. Male terminalia, dorsal view; 5. Male terminalia, dorsolateral view; 6. Epiproct, dorsal view; 7. Epiproct, lateral view; 8. Aedeagus, ventral view; 9. Male terminalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1018810/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="291">Figs. 5, 7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[844,872,1675,1698]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 11" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1358,1380]" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 11. Sweltsa hamula, sp. nov., paratype. 10. Male terminalia, dorsal view; 11. Male terminalia, dorsolateral view." pageId="0" pageNumber="291">11</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus membranous, apically with two fingershaped, hairy lobes (
<figureCitation box="[370,435,1707,1730]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1270,1292]" captionTargetBox="[317,1260,424,1241]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[313,1273,418,1249]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Sweltsa hamula, sp. nov., holotype. 1. Male habitus, dorsal view; 2. Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; 3. Wings; 4. Male terminalia, dorsal view; 5. Male terminalia, dorsolateral view; 6. Epiproct, dorsal view; 7. Epiproct, lateral view; 8. Aedeagus, ventral view; 9. Male terminalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1018810/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="291">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Tenth sternum broad and trapezoidal (
<figureCitation box="[860,926,1707,1730]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1270,1292]" captionTargetBox="[317,1260,424,1241]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[313,1273,418,1249]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Sweltsa hamula, sp. nov., holotype. 1. Male habitus, dorsal view; 2. Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; 3. Wings; 4. Male terminalia, dorsal view; 5. Male terminalia, dorsolateral view; 6. Epiproct, dorsal view; 7. Epiproct, lateral view; 8. Aedeagus, ventral view; 9. Male terminalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1018810/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="291">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1350,1986]" box="[199,408,1739,1762]" pageId="0" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,289,1739,1762]" pageId="0" pageNumber="291">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
